name: $code
desc: Returns: This list of codes represents the main clinical acts, such as a colonoscopy or an appendectomy, being documented. In some cases, the event is inherent in the typeCode, such as a "History and Physical Report" in which the procedure being documented is necessarily a "History and Physical" act.

name: $period
desc: Returns: The period of time covered by the documentation. There is no assertion that the documentation is a complete representation for this period, only that it documents events during this time.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The period of time covered by the documentation. There is no assertion that the documentation is a complete representation for this period, only that it documents events during this time.

name: $detail
desc: Returns: The description and/or reference of the event(s) being documented. For example, this could be used to document such a colonoscopy or an appendectomy.
